The paper discusses auctions and pricing mechanisms for online advertising, which involves topics related to game theory (cs.GT), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures (cs.DS), economics (cs.EC), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on position-based auctions, which are commonly used in online advertising, and proposes a new mechanism that generalizes current auctions and has desirable properties such as an envy-free Nash equilibrium. Therefore, cs.GT and cs.IR are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the auction and ranking aspects of the paper, followed by cs.DS and cs.EC which are also relevant to the optimization and economic aspects of the problem, and finally cs.LG which may be relevant to the machine learning techniques used in the paper.
